A stay at the Portswood Hotel captures a piece of Cape Town’s interesting history. The hotel’s restaurant and lobby are built around the original well and holding cells used by prisoners en route to Robben Island 300 years ago. Today, The Portswood is a deluxe hotel famous for its unique, personal approach to service. The hotel offers a choice of 59 twin rooms, 35 double rooms and 9 suites, all featuring modern facilities. The hotel’s Quarterdeck Restaurant specialises in Cape Malay infused cuisine, while The Terrace offers light meals and the Links Bar adjoins the outdoor pool. Perfectly positioned at the V & A Waterfront, The Portswood offers great value in a location that allows guests to walk to many sights, restaurants and entertainment options. This hotel is one of our top-selling Cape Town hotels.
